laboratory_examinations.findings: Large macro-arteriovenous fistula (MAVF) fed by the posterior spinal arteries of T-12 and L-1 on the left and L-2 on the right.
No residual filling of the varix; complete obliteration of the MAVF. Intact blood supply to the conus medullaris and lower thoracic spinal cord confirmed.
Reduction in size of the venous varix and resolution of perimedullary flow voids.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Partial resolution of spinal cord edema noted.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Complete resolution of T2 hyperintensity in the spinal cord; no abnormal perimedullary flow voids.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Hemosiderin deposits evident in the residual cavity of the venous varix.
